Token.Abstract: NSDictionary+RACPExtensions provides helper methods for interpreting the dictionary returned by the [NSData+RACPParser]
Checks if the RACP response details dictionary is a number of records response

ReturnValue.Abstract: YES if the response was to a report number of records operation, otherwise NO

Token.Abstract: Checks if the RACP response details dictionary is a general response

ReturnValue.Abstract: YES if the response was a general response, otherwise NO

Token.Abstract: Checks if the RACP response was a successful report records operation

ReturnValue.Abstract: YES if the response was to a successful report records operation, otherwise NO

Token.Abstract: Checks if the RACP response was a successful delete records operation

ReturnValue.Abstract: YES if the response was to a successful delete records operation, otherwise NO

Token.Abstract: Checks if the RACP response was a successful abort operation

ReturnValue.Abstract: YES if the response was to a successful abort operation, otherwise NO

Token.Abstract: Get the number of records from the RACP response details

ReturnValue.Abstract: Returns the number of stored records for the request, otherwise nil (RACP response is not a response to report number of records).

Token.Abstract: Get the RACP response op code

ReturnValue.Abstract: Only two possible op codes, report number of records response or general response. The values are defined in RACPConstants.h

Token.Abstract: Get the RACP request op code

ReturnValue.Abstract: The request op code is the operation just completed by the RACP and for which these response details are related to. The values are defined in RACPConstants.h

Token.Abstract: Get the RACP response code value

ReturnValue.Abstract: Returns the value of the response code. The values are defined in RACPConstants.h
